        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"Is this Chicago Sun-Times cover racist?";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:92:"http://www.chicagonow.com/red-cup-adventures/2015/08/is-this-chicago-sun-times-cover-racist/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://www.chicagonow.com/red-cup-adventures/2015/08/is-this-chicago-sun-times-cover-racist/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 06 Aug 2015 13:05:47 -0600";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://www.chicagonow.com/red-cup-adventures/?p=991";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9866:"I'm sick and tired of racist news coverage which paints Black and brown people as criminals and white people as misguided. When a Black person murders an innocent person, the murderer is instantly labeled a gang member even if the murderer haven't yet been identified by the police. When a white person murders an innocent people, the white murder is labeled as misguided. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/17/us/charleston-shooting-dylann-roof-troubled-past.html?_r=0">Dylann Roof is described as young man accused of the terrible crime. [He] was a bug-eyed boy with a bowl haircut who came from a broken home and attended at least seven schools in nine years.</a> Dylann Roof is a sick terrorist who killed Black people because he's a racist. But instead of the white news calling him a racist and terrorist, they discuss his broken home and how he must have a mental illness.

Since I'm sick of racist news coverage, I've started filtering the news I receive. I no longer watch the network TV news and I no longer buy newspapers because both TV and newspapers for so long have operated business with the "If it bleeds, it leads motto" and that way of business always unfairly spotlights crimes committed by the Black and brown. In filtering my news coverage, I listen to the morning show on WVON1690AM which is a Black news talk radio station in Chicago, read the free Red-Eye on my morning commute (if I'm going to get news from white media, I'm definitely not paying for it), and then I peruse social media and various blogs. If something is important, I usually know about it. But leaving the office yesterday, I was stopped dead in my tracks when I saw a young Black man's mugshot on the front page of the Chicago Sun-Times with the word GUILTY as the heading. I literally stopped walking when I saw the newspaper vending machine. I was so disgusted. I took out my phone, snapped a picture, and posted it on my Facebook page to see if I was the only one offended by this cover story. I soon learned that it wasn't just me.

Racism is like pornography in that I can't always describe the many forms in which it rears it's ugly head, but I definitely know it when I see it. In my opinion, this Chicago Sun-Times cover is racist. Once I got home, <a href="http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-chicago-cop-killing-trial-met-0731-20150730-story.html" target="_blank">I pulled up an article about Bryant Brewer</a>, the young man on the cover. (I pulled the article from the Chicago Tribune because me and the Sun-Times have broken up.) First, I didn't know this was a major story so that my first question as to why this young Black man's mugshot is on the cover. Secondly, the article I found describes a "Bizarre scene unfolds at cop killing trial as defendant takes stand...Judge Timothy Joyce, who will decide Brewer's fate, halted the trial at one point and ordered him removed from the courtroom after he repeatedly ignored orders to sit down on the witness stand. When testimony resumed, Brewer whispered his answers to the judge...Brewer was irate and lucid under cross-examination by a prosecutor after appearing confused, easily distracted and soft-spoken during questioning by his attorney...Brewer also gave contradictory and sometimes bizarre answers — testifying that he was a drug dealer before denying it moments later, even alleging he had previously "smoked weed" with a prosecution witness....'You've seen his behavior during the trial, chair dancing, laughing, he's in his own world,' his attorney, William Wolf, told reporters after the fourth day of trial. 'You now know he has mental problems, something he's probably had for most of his life.'" After white Dylann Roof executed 9 Black people, the white media quickly labeled him as having mental problems. Black Bryant Brewer is clearly having psychotic episodes in court, but the white media doesn't come to the conclusion that Mr. Brewer has a mental illness...he's just GUILTY.

From reading the article, it's clear to me that Bryant Brewer is probably a paranoid schizophrenic who shot police officer Thor Soderberg at the height of a mental delusion. My sincere condolences go out the family of the officer who was killed by Bryant Brewer, but sending someone with a serious mental illness to prison is not the answer. The Chicago Sun-Times should be ashamed of themselves for victimizing someone with mental illness and for contributing to the Demonization of Black Males. Sun-Times, yesterday's cover made you just as bad as Fox News...Congratulations if that's the type of smut journalism you were going for.

In the future, when media is a covering a trial, don't use a mugshot to sum everything up pictorially. Use a picture from the courtroom or honor the victim by using his/her picture. If you really feel Bryant Brewer was in his right mind when he shot Thor Soderberg, then use Mr. Soderberg's picture with the word JUSTICE. But JUSTICE was not served in this case as it is all to often not served when Black men come up against the Chicago Police Department. It's amazing how often evidence goes missing when it's a Black man vs. the CPD...evidence that would shed light on both sides of what happened that night...evidence that would support a Black man's self-defense narrative...it's just amazing how often that evidence goes missing.

The Chicago Tribune article also had a link to another article about the Chicago Police Department "<a href="http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-chicago-cop-killing-trial-met-0730-20150729-story.html" target="_blank">Expert unable to explain why police cameras missed fatal cop shooting</a>. Chicago police computer expert could not explain Wednesday why police security cameras failed to capture the fatal 2010 shooting of an officer outside an Englewood police deployment center. Attorneys for Bryant Brewer, who is on trial for the slaying of Officer Thor Soderberg, have emphasized the missing footage from two security cameras as they argue that Brewer acted in self-defense. The defense is also expected to argue that Brewer was insane at the time. He mumbled to himself for the third straight day at trial."

I volunteer as the Director of Marketing for the <a href="https://www.change.org/p/please-help-us-pardon-howard-morgan" target="_blank">Pardon Howard Morgan campaign</a>. Howard Morgan was a retired police officer working as a federal railroad officer in 2005 when he was pulled over for a minor traffic violation. Mr. Morgan, a Black man, was shot 28 times by 4 white Chicago Police Officers. Of the 28 shots received, 22 of those bullets were fired into his back. Mr. Morgan survived and was arrested for attempted murder. In the first trial, he was found innocent of firing his weapon. During Mr. Morgan's trial, numerous pieces of evidence were never found or were destroyed by the Chicago Police Department. For example, the van Mr. Morgan was driving that night which would have shown the ungodly amount of bullets fired at him by the CPD was destroyed while it was impounded in police custody. After the first trial, there was a hung jury on the attempted murder charge. You would think there wouldn't be a second trial because that violates the Double Jeopardy amendment, but there was a second trial. Mr. Morgan was shot 28 times and never fired his gun, but was given 40 years in prison for "attempted murder". I can just image Mr. Morgan's mugshot being splashed across the Chicago Sun-Times after his guilty verdict was read.

In case you don't know, the Chicago Police Department is out of control trying to assassinate the Black and brown men in Chicago. And the Chicago Sun-Times is GUILTY in demonizing Black men which then justifies the CPD's racism and assault. THE CHICAGO SUN-TIMES AND CHICAGO POLICE DEPARTMENT, I FIND YOU BOTH GUILTY OF CRIMES AGAINST THE BLACK AND BROWN PEOPLE OF CHICAGO. MAYOR RAHM EMANUEL, WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO ABOUT IT? DO BLACK LIVES MATTER IN CHICAGO?

Do you think the cover is racist? Let me know by leaving a comment.

